IMPORTANT POINTS
===================================

1. If the user creates a constructor inside the class then no default constructor is
   generated by the compiler.

2. this should be the first statement in the constructor and only in one constructor
   call should be used with the this() syntax.

3. Instance block invoked at the time of object creation

class Test{

   {
      System.out.println("IB1");
   }

   Test(){
      System.out.println("Hello");
   }
   Test(int a){
      System.out.println("Bolo");
   }

   public static void main (String args[]){
      Test t1 = new Test();
      Test t2 = new Test();

      // block will be called two times
   }
}

4. the static block is called only once at the time of loading the class
   and it is used to provide the value to the instance variables

5. A inner class is a part of nested class -> class inside another class
6. non static nested inner class is known as inner class
7. Inner class access all the members of the outer class

class Outer
{
     class Inner{
         void show(){
            System.out.println("The Inner class methods");
         }
     }
}

2 files will be created --> Outer.class and Outer$Inner.class